    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> over it so that it starts to wilt, then rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until cool, squeeze as much water out as you can and chop roughly</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> and <strong>Greek cheese </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>harissa paste</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>oregano</strong> and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>honey </strong>(save the rest for later!) – this is your <strong>cheese filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
